.TH CUPIDWM 1 VERSION
.SH NAME
cupidwm \- source-configured X11 tiling window manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cupidwm
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.RB [ \-\-print\-ipc\-socket ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
cupidwm is a compact source-configured X11 tiling window manager with
workspace-driven layouts, scratchpads, swallowing, and EWMH integration.
Configuration is compile-time through
.I config.h
and requires recompilation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-print\-ipc\-socket
Print the resolved IPC socket path based on
.I ipc_socket_path
and the current environment.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.def.h
Tracked default config template.
.TP
.I config.h
Local generated configuration used for builds.
.TP
.I /usr/share/xsessions/cupidwm.desktop
Display-manager session entry installed by
.B make install .
.SH IPC
IPC is disabled by default. Enable it with
.I ipc_enable
in
.I config.h
and use
.B cupidwmctl
to send commands.
The active socket path is published on the X root property
.B _CUPIDWM_IPC_SOCKET
when IPC is running.
.SH TESTING
Main validation targets:
.TP
.B make lint
Runs static analysis (`cppcheck`) and script linting (`shellcheck`) when installed.
.TP
.B make check
Builds sanitizer-enabled binary and runs Xephyr integration tests when dependencies are available.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
Optional external status commands execute via shell (`popen(3)`); keep
.I status_allow_external_cmd
disabled unless you trust the configured command.
Keep your system X11 libraries (including libX11) patched.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cupidwmctl (1),
.BR xprop (1),
.BR Xephyr (1)
